01:43:47,099 --> 01:43:48,953
Why should we be punished?

2185
01:44:00,985 --> 01:44:03,221
Moore: The union organizers
and the workers

2186
01:44:03,256 --> 01:44:06,802
prepared for a police assault
that was sure to come.

2187
01:44:06,841 --> 01:44:09,360
l'm gonna take the chance.

2188
01:44:09,400 --> 01:44:11,224
You're prepared to be arrested?

2189
01:44:11,256 --> 01:44:13,395
l am prepared to be arrested
if it's necessary.

2190
01:44:13,432 --> 01:44:17,229
We've been here since yesterday
and we aren't going anywhere.

2191
01:44:17,273 --> 01:44:19,029
We are committed to this.

2192
01:44:19,064 --> 01:44:21,300
Moore:
lt wasn't long before the media showed up.

2193
01:44:21,336 --> 01:44:24,118
And given the mood of the country
toward the bailout,

2194
01:44:24,152 --> 01:44:27,948
even the TV anchors had run out
of sympathy for the banks.

2195
01:44:27,992 --> 01:44:31,569
ln Chicago, a group of factory workers
watched like the rest of us

2196
01:44:31,606 --> 01:44:34,127
as taxpayers bailed out
the financial industry.

2197
01:44:34,167 --> 01:44:37,297
Now these laid-off workers
are demanding Bank of America

2198
01:44:37,335 --> 01:44:39,921
spend some of its
bailout money on them.

2199
01:44:39,958 --> 01:44:41,966
lt says ''Bank Robbers of America.''

2200
01:44:42,006 --> 01:44:45,038
Look, if we the taxpayers
are going to provide

2201
01:44:45,078 --> 01:44:47,948
a bailout for companies
like Bank of America,

2202
01:44:47,989 --> 01:44:50,739
then the least they can do
is use those funds

2203
01:44:50,774 --> 01:44:53,162
on American workers
and companies.

2204
01:44:53,206 --> 01:44:56,206
Woman:
$25 billion to Bank of America.

2205
01:44:56,244 --> 01:44:58,514
How do people sleep at night
when they act like that?

2206
01:44:58,548 --> 01:45:00,076
l don't get it.

2207
01:45:00,117 --> 01:45:01,939
Because what's the point
of bailing them out

2208
01:45:01,972 --> 01:45:04,525
if there aren't any jobs?

2209
01:45:04,564 --> 01:45:06,985
Moore:
The strike went on day after day.

2210
01:45:07,029 --> 01:45:09,679
The police had not yet come.

2211
01:45:09,716 --> 01:45:12,399
But the son of a Chicago
steelworker did.

2212
01:45:12,435 --> 01:45:16,429
He just also happened to be
the bishop in Chicago.

2213
01:45:16,467 --> 01:45:18,377
Ladies and gentlemen,

2214
01:45:18,420 --> 01:45:20,524
l am Bishop James Wilkowski.

2215
01:45:20,563 --> 01:45:23,628
l know that you are all undergoing

2216
01:45:23,667 --> 01:45:25,609
a great trial.

2217
01:45:25,650 --> 01:45:28,269
You are teaching

2218
01:45:28,306 --> 01:45:30,576
to our young people

2219
01:45:30,609 --> 01:45:32,551
that it is just

2220
01:45:32,595 --> 01:45:36,009
to challenge
that which is unfair.

2221
01:45:37,011 --> 01:45:40,939
l grew up on the far southeast
side of Chicago

2222
01:45:40,978 --> 01:45:42,636
and l saw what happened

2223
01:45:42,673 --> 01:45:45,869
when all the steel mills
disappeared.

2224
01:45:45,905 --> 01:45:48,654
And l saw the impact that it had

2225
01:45:48,689 --> 01:45:50,380
on families.

2226
01:45:50,417 --> 01:45:52,238
But this time

2227
01:45:52,273 --> 01:45:54,247
we are with you.

2228
01:45:54,288 --> 01:45:57,104
And we will not abandon you.

2229
01:45:57,136 --> 01:45:59,046
ln the name of the Father
and the Son

2230
01:45:59,088 --> 01:46:00,649
and the Holy Spirit.
Amen.

2231
01:46:00,688 --> 01:46:02,576
The body of Christ.

2232
01:46:04,783 --> 01:46:06,344
The body of Christ.

2233
01:46:08,783 --> 01:46:10,244
The body of Christ.

2234
01:46:12,494 --> 01:46:15,177
President Obama:
When it comes to the situation

2235
01:46:15,215 --> 01:46:18,475
here in Chicago
with the workers

2236
01:46:18,511 --> 01:46:22,220
who are asking for the benefits
and payments

2237
01:46:22,255 --> 01:46:24,840
that they have earned,
l think they're absolutely right.

2238
01:46:24,877 --> 01:46:28,261
( cheering )

2239
01:46:28,301 --> 01:46:31,432
What's happening to them
is reflective of what's happening

2240
01:46:31,470 --> 01:46:33,356
across this economy.

2241
01:46:33,390 --> 01:46:35,909
Reporter: He said, ''What's happening to
them is reflective of what's happening...''

2242
01:46:35,949 --> 01:46:37,804
Reporter #2: He said what is
happening to those workers

2243
01:46:37,837 --> 01:46:40,324
is reflective to what's happening
across this economy.

2244
01:46:40,365 --> 01:46:43,114
l was watching Obama's press
conference this morning.

2245
01:46:43,149 --> 01:46:45,353
l just got out of bed and decided

2246
01:46:45,389 --> 01:46:48,006
the best thing l could do
was to feed people.

2247
01:46:48,045 --> 01:46:49,474
So l brought some food.

2248
01:46:49,515 --> 01:46:51,720
- l brought some sandwiches.
- Oh, good.

2249
01:46:51,756 --> 01:46:55,399
Moore: ln fact, lots of Chicagoans
showed up to support the workers.

2250
01:46:55,435 --> 01:46:56,930
Reporter: The workers have become
a national symbol

2251
01:46:56,971 --> 01:46:58,913
for thousands of employees
laid off across the country.

2252
01:46:58,956 --> 01:47:01,095
Reporter #2: The sit-in has grabbed
the attention of politicians

2253
01:47:01,131 --> 01:47:04,612
who believe it exemplifies an imbalance
between a Wall Street

2254
01:47:04,650 --> 01:47:08,295
that gets government help
and a Main Street that gets the shaft.

2255
01:47:08,331 --> 01:47:10,239
Moore:
The question started to be asked:

2256
01:47:10,282 --> 01:47:12,649
Was this is the beginnings of a worker's
revolt against Wall Street?

2257
01:47:15,145 --> 01:47:17,185
The people united.

2258
01:47:17,225 --> 01:47:19,201
We'll never be defeated.

2259
01:47:19,242 --> 01:47:22,918
Bail out workers, not the banks.
Bail out workers, not the banks.

2260
01:47:22,953 --> 01:47:27,109
Moore: Pledges of financial support
and food showed up by the truckload.

2261
01:47:27,145 --> 01:47:30,375
Woman: lt's really beyond
what we had at first initially imagined.

2262
01:47:30,408 --> 01:47:33,091
And so now we're dreaming a little bit.

2263
01:47:33,128 --> 01:47:35,997
We even had a conversation--
well, what if we just tried

2264
01:47:36,041 --> 01:47:37,698
to run the factory like a cooperative?

2265
01:47:37,737 --> 01:47:39,677
We don't have any money.
We're not capitalists.

2266
01:47:39,720 --> 01:47:42,688
We're having those kind
of conversations

2267
01:47:42,728 --> 01:47:45,345
and the workers are thinking about it
and it's a difficult thing

2268
01:47:45,384 --> 01:47:47,555
'cause, you know, if you've been
told your whole life

2269
01:47:47,591 --> 01:47:50,755
that things are the way
other people tell you they are,

2270
01:47:50,792 --> 01:47:52,701
to be able to think
l can make it different

2271
01:47:52,743 --> 01:47:55,710
is quite a big deal.

2272
01:47:57,831 --> 01:48:00,382
We're all over the national news.
Everyone is watching you

2273
01:48:00,422 --> 01:48:03,618
because they're so inspired by you.
( speaks Spanish )

2274
01:48:06,181 --> 01:48:07,938
Moore:
After six days of the sit-in

2275
01:48:07,975 --> 01:48:11,073
Bank of America decided
enough was enough.

2276
01:48:11,109 --> 01:48:13,213
Better to pay off
these workers now

2277
01:48:13,253 --> 01:48:16,483
and hope their little
revolution goes away.

2278
01:48:16,516 --> 01:48:20,095
And so the bank and the company
agreed to all the worker's demands.

2279
01:48:20,132 --> 01:48:22,914
Yes we did!
Yes we did!

2280
01:48:22,948 --> 01:48:26,462
The average package for each worker

2281
01:48:26,501 --> 01:48:30,210
will be very close to $6,000.

2282
01:48:30,244 --> 01:48:33,342
But this is about more
than just money.

2283
01:48:33,380 --> 01:48:36,697
lt's about what can be achieved

2284
01:48:36,739 --> 01:48:40,569
when workers organize
and stand up for justice.

2285
01:48:40,612 --> 01:48:42,587
Just to fight--
fight fight fight fight fight

2286
01:48:42,627 --> 01:48:44,896
just to get the most basic thing

2287
01:48:44,930 --> 01:48:46,622
that people should take for granted

2288
01:48:46,658 --> 01:48:50,302
and that's legally theirs.

2289
01:48:50,338 --> 01:48:54,179
We just fight so hard just for
the most basic things in life.

2290
01:48:56,386 --> 01:48:59,386
Moore: lt's a fight we knew
all too well in Flint, Michigan.

2291
01:48:59,426 --> 01:49:02,654
For it was here that my uncle
and his fellow workers

2292
01:49:02,689 --> 01:49:05,307
first brought down the mighty
corporate interests

2293
01:49:05,345 --> 01:49:06,939
that dominated their lives.

2294
01:49:09,088 --> 01:49:12,350
lt was the day before
New Year's Eve in 1936.

2295
01:49:12,385 --> 01:49:15,680
Hundreds of men and women
took over the GM factories in Flint

2296
01:49:15,712 --> 01:49:17,948
and occupied them for 44 days.

2297
01:49:19,744 --> 01:49:22,972
They were the first union that beat
an industrial corporation.

2298
01:49:23,007 --> 01:49:25,212
And their actions eventually resulted

2299
01:49:25,247 --> 01:49:27,614
in the creation of a middle class.

2300
01:49:27,648 --> 01:49:30,648
But back in these days of the Flint
sit-down strike,

2301
01:49:30,686 --> 01:49:34,842
the police and the company thugs
were not going to just stand by.

2302
01:49:34,878 --> 01:49:38,326
After a bloody battle one evening,
the Governor of Michigan,

2303
01:49:38,367 --> 01:49:41,399
with the support of the President
of the United States

2304
01:49:41,439 --> 01:49:45,082
Franklin Roosevelt,
sent in the National Guard.

2305
01:49:45,118 --> 01:49:48,979
But the guns of the soldiers
weren't used on the workers.

2306
01:49:49,021 --> 01:49:50,614
They were pointed at the police

2307
01:49:50,654 --> 01:49:52,541
and the hired goons,

2308
01:49:52,573 --> 01:49:55,956
warning them to leave
these workers alone.

2309
01:49:57,054 --> 01:49:59,770
For Mr. Roosevelt believed
that the men inside

2310
01:49:59,805 --> 01:50:03,797
had a right to a redress
of their grievances.

2311
01:50:05,085 --> 01:50:08,184
Seven years later,
President Roosevelt was too sick

2312
01:50:08,220 --> 01:50:11,896
to go up to the Capitol and give his
annual State of the Union Address.

2313
01:50:11,931 --> 01:50:13,688
Ladies and gentlemen,

2314
01:50:13,725 --> 01:50:16,474
the President of the United States.

2315
01:50:16,507 --> 01:50:20,850
lt has been my custom to deliver
these annual messages in person.

2316
01:50:20,891 --> 01:50:23,793
Moore: So he gave it from
the White House over the radio.

2317
01:50:23,835 --> 01:50:26,769
When it was over he asked
the newsreel cameras

2318
01:50:26,811 --> 01:50:29,746
to step into his room because he
wanted the American people

2319
01:50:29,787 --> 01:50:33,266
to see one particular part
of his speech.

2320
01:50:33,306 --> 01:50:36,787
The President of the United States
then took the radical step

2321
01:50:36,826 --> 01:50:39,411
of proposing a second Bill of Rights

2322
01:50:39,449 --> 01:50:40,791
to the Constitution.

2323
01:50:40,826 --> 01:50:44,305
ln our day certain economic truths

2324
01:50:44,345 --> 01:50:47,411
have become accepted
as self-evident.

2325
01:50:47,449 --> 01:50:49,904
A second Bill of Rights

2326
01:50:49,945 --> 01:50:53,556
under which a new basis of security
and prosperity

2327
01:50:53,592 --> 01:50:55,764
can be established for all

2328
01:50:55,801 --> 01:50:59,345
regardless of station
or race or creed.

2329
01:50:59,385 --> 01:51:02,068
Among these are:

2330
01:51:02,104 --> 01:51:05,900
The right to a useful
and remunerative job;

2331
01:51:05,944 --> 01:51:09,260
The right to earn enough to provide
adequate food

2332
01:51:09,302 --> 01:51:10,796
and clothing and recreation;

2333
01:51:10,840 --> 01:51:13,261
The right of every farmer

2334
01:51:13,302 --> 01:51:15,636
to raise and sell his products

2335
01:51:15,671 --> 01:51:18,671
at a return which will
give him and his family

2336
01:51:18,711 --> 01:51:20,979
a decent living;

2337
01:51:21,015 --> 01:51:24,789
The right of every businessman
large and small

2338
01:51:24,822 --> 01:51:28,051
to trade in an atmosphere of freedom,

2339
01:51:28,087 --> 01:51:31,631
freedom from unfair competition
and domination

2340
01:51:31,670 --> 01:51:34,670
by monopolies at home or abroad;

2341
01:51:34,710 --> 01:51:38,025
The right of every family
to a decent home;

2342
01:51:38,069 --> 01:51:41,548
The right to adequate medical care

2343
01:51:41,588 --> 01:51:45,331
and the opportunity to achieve
and enjoy good health;

2344
01:51:45,364 --> 01:51:48,560
The right to adequate protection

2345
01:51:48,596 --> 01:51:51,858
from the economic fears
of old age,

2346
01:51:51,891 --> 01:51:54,280
sickness, accidents

2347
01:51:54,323 --> 01:51:56,079
and unemployment;

2348
01:51:56,115 --> 01:51:59,051
The right to a good education.

2349
01:51:59,091 --> 01:52:03,314
All of these rights spell security.

2350
01:52:03,347 --> 01:52:06,250
And after this war is won,

2351
01:52:06,291 --> 01:52:09,520
we must be prepared
to move forward

2352
01:52:09,555 --> 01:52:12,521
in the implementation
of these rights

2353
01:52:12,561 --> 01:52:16,173
to new goals of human happiness
and wellbeing.

2354
01:52:16,210 --> 01:52:20,520
For unless there is security
here at home,

2355
01:52:20,561 --> 01:52:25,198
there cannot be lasting peace
in the world.

2356
01:52:34,256 --> 01:52:37,421
Moore: Roosevelt would be dead
in little over a year.

2357
01:52:40,113 --> 01:52:43,309
He would not live to see
the end of the war.

2358
01:52:43,344 --> 01:52:47,020
Nor would there be any enactment
of his new Bill of Rights.

2359
01:52:54,190 --> 01:52:57,060
Had he lived and succeeded,

2360
01:52:57,103 --> 01:52:59,340
every American,
regardless of race,

2361
01:52:59,375 --> 01:53:02,375
would have had a right
to a decent job...

2362
01:53:05,198 --> 01:53:06,725
a livable wage...

2363
01:53:09,198 --> 01:53:10,539
universal health care...

2364
01:53:12,493 --> 01:53:14,152
a good education...

2365
01:53:16,493 --> 01:53:18,565
an affordable home...

2366
01:53:20,621 --> 01:53:22,792
a paid vacation...

2367
01:53:26,444 --> 01:53:28,965
and an adequate pension.

2368
01:53:31,692 --> 01:53:34,180
None of this would come to pass.

2369
01:53:36,171 --> 01:53:40,328
No American would be
guaranteed any of this.

2370
01:53:43,787 --> 01:53:46,307
But the people of Europe and Japan

2371
01:53:46,346 --> 01:53:48,932
got every one of these rights.

2372
01:53:48,970 --> 01:53:51,524
How did that happen?

2373
01:53:51,563 --> 01:53:56,101
After the war, the people
of Roosevelt's administration

2374
01:53:56,137 --> 01:53:58,984
went overseas
to help rebuild Europe.

2375
01:53:59,018 --> 01:54:02,846
During this time new constitutions
were written

2376
01:54:02,890 --> 01:54:07,167
for the defeated nations
of Germany, ltaly and Japan.

2377
01:54:07,210 --> 01:54:09,795
The ltalian constitution

2378
01:54:09,832 --> 01:54:12,680
guaranteed all women equal rights.

2379
01:54:12,712 --> 01:54:15,395
And this was 1947.

2380
01:54:15,432 --> 01:54:19,426
The German constitution
said that the state has the right

2381
01:54:19,465 --> 01:54:22,760
to take over property
and the means of production

2382
01:54:22,792 --> 01:54:24,614
for the common good.

2383
01:54:24,648 --> 01:54:27,582
And here's what we wrote up
for the Japanese.

2384
01:54:27,623 --> 01:54:30,885
All workers have a right
to organize into a union.

2385
01:54:30,920 --> 01:54:34,596
And academic freedom
is guaranteed.

2386
01:54:34,631 --> 01:54:37,380
For the next 65 years

2387
01:54:37,414 --> 01:54:39,389
we would not become the country

2388
01:54:39,430 --> 01:54:41,252
that Roosevelt wanted us to be.

2389
01:54:42,375 --> 01:54:45,886
lnstead, we became this...

2390
01:54:53,158 --> 01:54:55,743
l remember thinking
during the Katrina flood,

2391
01:54:55,782 --> 01:54:57,636
''Why is it always the poor

2392
01:54:57,668 --> 01:54:59,425
who have to suffer the misery?

2393
01:54:59,462 --> 01:55:01,796
Why isn't it ever Bernie Madoff
up on the roof

2394
01:55:01,828 --> 01:55:03,454
screaming for help?

2395
01:55:03,493 --> 01:55:05,184
Or the head of Citibank

2396
01:55:05,220 --> 01:55:08,569
or the hedge fund guys
at Goldman Sachs?

2397
01:55:08,613 --> 01:55:11,579
Or the CEO at AlG?''

2398
01:55:11,619 --> 01:55:13,759
lt never is these guys, is it?

2399
01:55:13,796 --> 01:55:17,373
lt's always those who
never got a slice of the pie

2400
01:55:17,412 --> 01:55:19,615
because these men
took it all

2401
01:55:19,652 --> 01:55:21,789
and left them with nothing,

2402
01:55:21,828 --> 01:55:23,518
left them to die.

2403
01:55:25,954 --> 01:55:28,637
l refuse to live in a country like this.

2404
01:55:28,675 --> 01:55:30,682
And l'm not leaving.

2405
01:55:44,033 --> 01:55:47,229
We live in the richest
country in the world.

2406
01:55:47,265 --> 01:55:50,712
We all deserve a decent job,

2407
01:55:50,753 --> 01:55:54,364
healthcare, a good education,

2408
01:55:54,400 --> 01:55:57,498
a home to call our own.

2409
01:55:57,536 --> 01:55:59,957
We all deserve FDR's dream.

2410
01:56:01,536 --> 01:56:03,707
And it's a crime that we don't have it.

2411
01:56:04,927 --> 01:56:06,488
And we never will,

2412
01:56:06,528 --> 01:56:09,844
as long as we have a system
that enriches the few

2413
01:56:09,887 --> 01:56:12,189
at the expense of the many.

2414
01:56:13,792 --> 01:56:16,247
Capitalism is an evil.

2415
01:56:16,287 --> 01:56:18,261
And you cannot regulate evil.

2416
01:56:20,287 --> 01:56:23,930
You have to eliminate it
and replace it with something

2417
01:56:23,966 --> 01:56:26,868
that is good for all people.

2418
01:56:26,911 --> 01:56:30,707
And that something
is called democracy.

2419
01:56:43,132 --> 01:56:45,555
Crimes have been committed
in this building.

2420
01:56:45,596 --> 01:56:48,247
l am here to make a citizen's arrest.

2421
01:56:48,284 --> 01:56:51,634
Please come down
and step away from the building.

2422
01:56:51,676 --> 01:56:53,782
Do not be afraid.

2423
01:56:53,819 --> 01:56:56,635
Federal prison is a nice place.

2424
01:57:00,539 --> 01:57:03,386
You know,
l can't really do this anymore

2425
01:57:03,418 --> 01:57:06,288
unless those of you who
are watching this in the theater

2426
01:57:06,332 --> 01:57:08,305
want to join me.

2427
01:57:08,346 --> 01:57:10,288
l hope you will.

2428
01:57:10,331 --> 01:57:12,948
And please, speed it up.

2429
01:57:14,681 --> 01:57:18,457
Arise ye workers
from your slumber

2430
01:57:18,489 --> 01:57:21,752
Arise ye prisoners of want,
